10 term, "state certified," "state licensed," or words of substantially similar
11 meaning;[ or]
12 (c) Assume or use any title, designation, or abbreviation likely to create the
13 impression of certification or licensure by the state as a real property[estate]
14 appraiser firm, partnership, or corporation; or
15 (d) Use the title "real property appraiser," "real estate appraiser," or
16 "appraiser" in relation to real property or federally related transactions.
17 (2) A certificate holder or licensee shall not assume or use any title, designation, or
18 abbreviation likely to create the impression of certification or licensure by the board
19 other than the correct type of certification or licensure.
20 (3) Each certificate holder or licensee who is a resident of Kentucky shall have and
21 maintain a definite place of business in this state, a current email[e-mail] address,
22 and a current telephone number. A nonresident is not required to maintain an active
23 place of business in this state if a definite place of business is maintained in the
24 state where the nonresident resides. A nonresident shall maintain a current email[e-
