6 use of agricultural land in Kentucky for farming purposes by granting a tax credit to
7 a seller who agrees to sell agricultural assets to an actively engaged farmer or a
8 beginning farmer.
9 (4) A seller wanting to sell agricultural assets may be eligible for a tax credit up to five
10 percent (5%) of the selling price of qualifying agricultural assets, subject to:
11 (a) A twenty-five thousand dollar ($25,000) cap for each taxable year of the seller
12 when agricultural assets are sold to an actively engaged farmer who does not
13 meet the definition of a beginning farmer;
14 (b) A fifty thousand dollar ($50,000) cap for each taxable year of the seller when
15 agricultural assets are sold to a beginning farmer;
16 (c) A one hundred thousand dollar ($100,000) lifetime cap for each seller selling
17 to an actively engaged farmer;
18 (d) A two hundred thousand dollar ($200,000) lifetime cap for each seller selling
19 to a beginning farmer; and
20 (e) A proration by the authority based on the overall cap shared between the
21 Small Business Tax Credit Program and the Selling Farmer Tax Credit
22 Program cap of three million dollars ($3,000,000) under KRS 154.60-020.
